beverly lahaye from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search beverly lahaye born beverly jean ratcliffe 19290430 april 30 1929 age 88 detroit michigan us residence los angeles california nationality american alma mater bob jones university office chair of concerned women for america political party republican spouses tim lahaye m 19472016 his death children linda murphy vicechairman concerned women for america b 1948 larry lahaye lee lahaye cfo concerned women for america lori lahaye scheck beverly lahaye born april 30 1929 is an american christian conservative activist and author who founded concerned women for america cwa in san diego california in 1979 and is the organizations current chair she was the wife of the late evangelical christian minister and prolific author of the left behind series timothy lahaye they had been married 69 years the cwa is a 501c3 public policy women’s organization1 contents 1 life and education 2 published works 3 concerned women for america cwa 4 bibliography 5 references 6 external links life and educationedit beverly jean ratcliffe was born in detroit michigan on april 30 1929 she attended bob jones university and met tim lahaye while a student there she married tim on july 5 1947 her oldest daughter linda murphy was born in 1948 and is the vicechairman of concerned women for america her oldest son is larry lahaye lee lahaye was her youngest son and the cfo of concerned women for america he is now deceased her youngest daughter is lori lahaye scheck they have four children and nine grandchildren and live in the los angeles area in 1992 jerry falwells liberty university gave her an honorary doctorate of humanities published worksedit lahaye wrote the spiritcontrolled woman and the desires of a womans heart lahaye has cowritten multiple books with terri blackstock2 she and her husband coauthored the act of marriage the beauty of sexual love in 1976 concerned women for america cwaedit initially cwa was a reaction to the national organization for women and a 1978 barbara walters interview with feminist betty friedan3 lahaye stated of the interview that she was convinced friedan’s goal was a misguided attempt to dismantle the bedrock of american culture the family4 and that she believed christian women were not included in discussions of womens rights she held a rally in a local san diego auditorium which marked the beginning of cwa4 while cwa was originally intended to be a local group the organization was established nationwide within two years5 bibliographyedit how to develop your childs temperament 1977 oclc 3312367 i am a woman by gods design 1980 oclc 6813275 the act of marriage the beauty of sexual love 1976 oclc 1859880 the spiritcontrolled woman 1976 oclc 3033275 the restless woman 1984 oclc 10912698 referencesedit concerned women for america fact checkorg october 2010 retrieved 14 september 2013 mrs beverly lahaye founder and chairman cwa concerned women for america archived from the original on 10 september 2004 retrieved 12 february 2011  gardiner s concerned women for america a case study feminism and womens studies 28 august 2006 online as of 19 april 2007 a b beverly lahaye marks three decades of promoting traditional values through cwa archived 20130919 at the wayback machine christian examinercom 20 december 09 retrieved 14 september 2013 henry tamara september 2 1992 group says school censorship increasing associated press retrieved 12 february 2011  external linksedit the beverly lahaye institute about beverly lahaye beverly lahayes political donations at the wayback machine archived march 8 2005 appearances on cspan authority control worldcat identities viaf 85374323 lccn n50039407 isni 0000 0001 1450 462x iath w62j7vbf retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlebeverlylahayeoldid802684227 categories 1929 births living people american nonprofit executives american prolife activists intelligent design advocates protestant writers california republicans wome